manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: QUICTO 2PCS Car Seat Storage Hanging Bag, Multi-Pocket Seat Side Organizer, Car Multifunctional Storage Mesh Net Pocket, Can Hold Mobile Phone, Wallet QUICTO 2PCS Car Seat Storage Hanging Bag, Multi-Pocket Seat Side Organizer, Car Multifunctional Storage Mesh Net Pocket, Can Hold Mobile Phone, Wallet SIZE: Our car seat side organizer bag measures 31.1 inches; this stretchable organizer bag is durable and flexible, fits most car and SUV seats.MULTIFUNCTIONAL: Our multifunctional car seat organizer hanging bag can store or organize a lot of small things, such as wallet, cell phone, charging cable, change, soda, etc.EASY TO FIND: Small items like change that you use often can be found at any time without worrying about dropping them to those hard to reach places in the car, very practical.

Design of stretchable elastic belt This organizer bag of ours is designed with a retractable elastic band, which is great for keeping it secured to the sides of your seat without wobbling or falling off. Two retractable mesh pockets This side organizer bag has two retractable mesh pockets for snacks, cell phones, charging cables, keys and other small items that can be removed and used at any time. One zippered sealed pocket There's also a zippered, sealed pocket for storing some coins, wallets, or cans of beverages, etc., so you can just pull them out when you need coins without having to keep searching for them in the center console and other places. High quality tarpaulin and zipper We made it with 600D Oxford cloth + encrypted mesh, perfect zipper won't snag anything, good privacy, very practical!

Installation Step 1: 1. Slip the top telescoping strap of the organizer bag over the seat headrest. Installation Step 2: 2. Place it vertically on the side of the seat for a comfortable fit. Installation Step 3: 3. Stretch the telescopic strap at the lower end of the product down under the seat and attach it to the seat corner to secure it. Installation Step 4: 4. Finish installing it to organize anything you have in your car.
Our 2pcs Car Seat Storage Hanging Bag is perfect for everyday use and very easy to install.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Pretty Small & Moves Around
reviews.reviewText: For the price these are great but they're pretty small, dont hold a lot and they sometimes slide around. but im pretty happy with them and im gonna keep em.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Easy to install
reviews.reviewText: Material and elastic is cheap and thin. Zippwred pockets aren't super deep, but work well for small lightweight items. Open pocket is large enough to tuck in most cell phones.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not THE most helpful...
reviews.reviewText: Nice points:It's compact indeed.It's made to fit a more convenient space.Not so pleasant points:It's a little too compact for what I'd hope to use it for.It holds very little, the compartments are super small.It doesn't always hold its position well, it slips to the back or front on occasion.The middle pockets barely fits an inhaler...I kept it and chose to rearrange what I keep in it.It helps a bit, but not at all what I had in mind upon purchase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fit perfectly and so useful
reviews.reviewText: I got these because it was a good price for two and because I became a neat freak with my car. These help organize extra items I have lying around and my friends sitting in the back can keep their phones in the pockets while connected to the AUX. Good for camping and organizing little things. I can fill them with hand sanitizer mini bottles, wipes, tissues, the possibilities are endless. I have both on my front car seats and they fit my 2005 Toyota matrix perfectly. I would say they are not perfectly straight on the chairs due to their incline and the bottom loop is attached in a wonky way to the bottom of the chair. It works, though!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Just what I orderdd
reviews.reviewText: Fit my truck great.Good storage option

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Too long for my 2017 Traverse
reviews.reviewText: I bought these hoping to use them on the back captain chairs in the middle row. I thought they would work well to allow my teen to have a place to put her things within reach for long road trips. They were entirely too long to fit on the front seat or the captain chairs in the center row. This was a shame as I was truly looking forward to a place to keep things, like the remote / head phones for the rear entertainment center.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars They don’t stay in place and don’t hold much.
reviews.reviewText: I had read the reviews that they are small and that they surely are! So small I can’t even fit my inhaler in them and I had wanted to use them for cell phones. I only put one on because really all they hold are small cords for me. Anything else that fits flips out of it so no idea what people might use these for.Another issue I have noticed is that they spin aroundTo the front so the person getting into the seat needs to move it back or rest their back on it. I supposeI could shorten the to fix that issue but I really doubt I will use it that long.

reviews.reviewText: A bit smaller than what I was expecting, the material is good, and the zippers zip well.
